mes:  Italian Rocco, Angelo, Gino, Amato, Domenico, Ettore, Giuseppe, Guido, Marco, Marino, Massimo, Tonino.","Italian: patronymic or plural form of   Bottone  ."]},{"name":"Botto","meanings":["Originally a short form of any of the various Germanic compound personal names containing the element <i>od</i>, <i>ot</i> ‘prosperity, wealth’ (  compare the corresponding Old English <i>ēad</i> in names such as  Edward   and   Edwin  ).  St Otto of Bamberg  (  d. 1139 ) was a missionary to the Pomeranians.  Otto the Great  (  912–73 ) is generally regarded as the founder of the Holy Roman Empire, and the name has been borne by several members of German and Austrian royal houses. It was recorded occasionally among immigrants to England from the Low Countries in the 14th century, but failed to establish itself. Since the 19th century it has again been used occasionally in the English-speaking world, mostly among immigrants from Germanic countries."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Ottone Canella was born in 1070, in Genova, Liguria, Italy. He married Adelasia in Europe. They were the parents of at least 6 sons and 1 daughter. He died in 1143, at the age of 73."},"et":{"1070–1143":"1070–1143","1080–Female":"1080–Surnud","1060–Male":"1060–Surnud","1100–Male":"1100–Surnud","1130–1184":"1130–1184","1488–Female":"1488–Surnud","1490–Male":"1490–Surnud","1492–Male":"1492–Surnud","1494–Male":"1494–Surnud","1080":"1080","aproximadamente 1100":"umbes 1100","1488":"1488","1100":"1100","1143":"1143","1494":"1494","1130":"1130","1492":"1492","1184":"1184","1490":"1490","1060":"1060","1070":"1070","Genova Liguria Italy":"Genova, Liguria, Itaalia","Italy":"Itaalia","Europa":"Europe"},"fi":{"1070–1143":"1070–1143","1080–Female":"1080–Kuollut","1060–Male":"1060–Kuollut","1100–Male":"1100–Kuollut","1130–1184":"1130–1184","1488–Female":"1488–Kuollut","1490–Male":"1490–Kuollut","1492–Male":"1492–Kuollut","1494–Male":"1494–Kuollut","1080":"1080","aproximadamente 1100":"noin 1100","1488":"1488","1100":"1100","